gobblin.runtime.job_exec

Class JobLauncherExecutionDriver

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.FutureTask<JobExecutionResult>
      • gobblin.runtime.job_exec.JobLauncherExecutionDriver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ListenableFuture<JobExecutionResult>, JobExecutionDriver, JobExecutionStateListenerContainer, Runnable, Future<JobExecutionResult>, RunnableFuture<JobExecutionResult>

    public class JobLauncherExecutionDriver
extends FutureTask<JobExecutionResult>
implements JobExecutionDriver
    An implementation of JobExecutionDriver which acts as an adapter to the legacy JobLauncher API.

      • create

        public static JobLauncherExecutionDriver create(Configurable sysConfig,
                                                JobSpec jobSpec,
                                                Optional<JobLauncherFactory.JobLauncherType> jobLauncherType,
                                                Optional<org.slf4j.Logger> log,
                                                boolean instrumentationEnabled,
                                                JobExecutionLauncher.StandardMetrics launcherMetrics,
                                                SharedResourcesBroker<GobblinScopeTypes> instanceBroker)
        Creates a new JobExecutionDriver which acts as an adapter to the legacy JobLauncher API.
        Parameters:
        sysConfig - the system/environment config
        jobSpec - the JobSpec to be executed
        jobLauncherType - an optional jobLauncher type; the value follows the convention of JobLauncherFactory#newJobLauncher(java.util.Properties, java.util.Properties, String). If absent, {@link JobLauncherFactory#newJobLauncher(java.util.Properties, java.util.Properties)} will be used which looks for the {@link ConfigurationKeys#JOB_LAUNCHER_TYPE_KEY} in the system configuration.
        jobExecStateListener - an optional listener to listen for state changes in the execution.
        log - an optional logger to be used; if none is specified, a default one will be instantiated.

      • registerWeakStateListener

        public void registerWeakStateListener(JobExecutionStateListener listener)
        Description copied from interface: JobExecutionStateListenerContainer
        Like JobExecutionStateListenerContainer.registerStateListener(JobExecutionStateListener) but it will create a weak reference. The implementation will automatically remove the listener registration once the listener object gets GCed.

        Note that weak listeners cannot be removed using JobExecutionStateListenerContainer.unregisterStateListener(JobExecutionStateListener).

        Specified by:
        registerWeakStateListener in interface JobExecutionStateListenerContainer
